          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To specify a list of offsets, call the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLRenderCommandEncoder/setVertexAmplificationCount(_:viewMappings:)",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " method.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "When your app renders to different render targets, you specify the render target index to render to in your vertex shader by adding the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "render_target_array_index",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " attribute to one of the vertex shaderâ€™s outputs. If you are using vertex amplification, Metal calculates the index for each amplified vertex by adding the index offset for the vertex to the value returned from your shader.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
